{
  "texts": [
    "Specifically, we refer to the chart-task space types summarized in visualization literacy research [36] (see Table 4).With collected tables, former works have explored generating charts and QA pairs using LLMs [24,57].",
    "However, they overlook potential quality distortions arising from the instability inherent in language model outputs, nor has it considered guiding the generative process through an informed understanding of the chart space.",
    "We harness LLMs' in-context learning ability to follow the visualization reference process [9], ensuring the variety of the resulting charts and thus covering the chart space.",
    "Figure 6 outlines our chart generation pipeline, which encompasses two phases: Retrieval-Augmented Chart Generation and Visualization-Referenced Encoding Augmentation.",
    "Templates of prompts constructed for LLM input in this section can be found in Supplementary Section S1."
  ]
}